    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-vr-stiffness-primary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. N=11 experimental constructs",
      "description": "This result encapsulates the full multi-laboratory validation exercise for construct stiffness. Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested at two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH OSEL biomechanics lab and DePuy Synthes test facility) under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading. Each specimen was loaded to 40 mm displacement at 5 mm/min crosshead speed with a 100 mm rod segment and L4–L5 block height. FEA predictions from three independently implemented models (FDA Abaqus/Standard 2020, Ansys Mechanical 2021 R1, DePuy Synthes Abaqus 2019) were compared against each experimental replicate. The validation metric E/uval was computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3.2 using combined model and experimental uncertainty. All eleven comparisons yielded E/uval < 1.96 and percentage differences < 10%, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance criteria. The detailed derivation of experimental uncertainty (uexp = 3.2% CV) and model form uncertainty (umodel = 4.8%) is documented in the accompanying validation report NRJ-2024-VAL-001. This result carries the most comprehensive narrative documentation of the validation exercise and is the primary evidence supporting the credibility claim.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-bench-n11-lab1"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-vr-yield-force",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental mean",
      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force compared against experimentally measured yield force across N=11 constructs. Mean experimental yield force 412 N (SD 18 N); FEA ensemble mean 398 N. Percentage difference 3.4%, E/uval = 0.87. Acceptance criterion met.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-bench-n11-lab2",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/nagaraja-fea-run-yield-force-comparison-2024"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-vr-force-at-40mm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental",
      "description": "FEA-predicted force at 40 mm displacement compared against experimental values. Mean experimental 1 048 N (SD 42 N); FEA ensemble mean 1 021 N. Percentage difference 2.6%, E/uval = 0.74. Acceptance criterion met.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-bench-n11-lab1",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/nagaraja-fea-run-force-40mm-comparison-2024"
    }
  ],
